quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,88,"Then he cast a glance at the stars,"
  37,89,"And he said: ",1:[{37:89} See the footnote (C) of (Verse 16:121).]
  37,90,"So they turned away from him, and departed (for fear of the disease)."
  38,67,"Say: "
  38,68,""
  38,69,""
  39,52,"Do they not know that Allâh enlarges the provision for whom He wills, and straitens it (for whom He wills). Verily, in this are signs for the folk who believe!"
  39,53,"Say: ",1:[{39:53}]
  39,54,""
  40,31,""
  40,32,""
  40,33,"A Day when you will turn your backs and flee having no protector from Allâh. And whomsoever Allâh sends astray, for him there is no guide."
  41,10,"He placed therein (i.e. the earth) firm mountains from above it, and He blessed it, and measured therein its sustenance (for its dwellers) in four Days equal (i.e. all these four days were equal in the length of time) for all those who ask (about its creation)."
  41,11,"Then He rose over (Istawâ) towards the heaven when it was smoke, and said to it and to the earth: "
  41,12,"Then He completed and finished from their creation (as) seven heavens in two Days and He made in each heaven its affair. And We adorned the nearest (lowest) heaven with lamps (stars){1} to be an adornment as well as to guard (from the devils by using them as missiles against the devils). Such is the Decree of Him the All-Mighty, the All-Knower.",1:[{41:12} See the footnote of (Verse 6:97).]
